			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We know of the following uses of mprotect() so far:
 * Guard pages for the stack (can be done with MAP_FIXED instead)
 * Used by glibc's arena.c to allocate heaps (can also be done with MAP_FIXED) -- issue 1042
 * Used by the dynamic linker for "relro" pages -- those which can be made read-only after performing relocations at load time.  This is a security/robustness feature.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-10-15T12:12:15.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-15T12:12:15.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=895#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/895/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>